The paper deals with channel feedback mechanisms in massive MIMO systems, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a classification algorithm based on statistical separability, which falls under the Statistical Learning (cs.SI) sub-category. The paper also deals with precoding methods, which are studied in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with multi-input multi-output (MIMO) systems, which are studied in the Signal Processing (cs.SP) sub-category, but this is less likely given the focus on feedback mechanisms.
